Sure, I can help you with a sample letter for an annual feedback meeting. Please keep in mind that this letter is just an example and should be modified and customized to meet your specific needs and circumstances.

[Your Name]
[Your Address]
[City, State ZIP Code]
[Your Email Address]
[Date]

[Employee Name]
[Employee Address]
[City, State ZIP Code]

Dear [Employee Name],

I would like to invite you to our annual feedback meeting, which will be held on [date] at [time] at [location]. During this meeting, we will be discussing your performance over the past year and providing feedback on your achievements and areas for improvement.

We appreciate your hard work and dedication to our organization over the past year, and we believe that this feedback meeting is an important opportunity for us to reflect on your accomplishments and discuss your goals for the upcoming year. We would like to take this opportunity to recognize your strengths and provide guidance on areas where you can further develop your skills and performance.

Please come prepared to discuss your progress and share your thoughts and feedback on your performance. We encourage you to bring any questions or concerns you may have so that we can have an open and honest discussion about your work.

We look forward to meeting with you and having a productive conversation about your performance. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to contact me directly.

Sincerely,

[Your Name]
